The paper discusses a machine learning algorithm (mean field) and its conversion into a feedforward network, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of the mean field network as an inference tool and discriminative model, which falls under the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of tied weights and untying weights in the network, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY).
